I am a custom contractor and been using or trying to use Thumbtack for years. My business is 95% referral and we are generally 75% awarded on projects we estimate...until Thumbtack came along. Great idea and probably worth it if bigger jobs were rewarded. We do excellent work and survived 20+ years based on customer service and above standard execution. We use it get smaller jobs to fill in the timeline gaps. As of late, we barely even get any responses and it could be because we do not have any reviews or we look too expensive. Getting customers to leave reviews is a full time job in itself even if you do a first class job and offer discounts for reviews. Seems to be a lot of tire kickers or people just trying to get a sense of what some services cost. It takes a lot of our time to come measure jobs and give them an estimate just so they know what it may cost. In a world of declining value and dying customer service, thumbtack, although maybe not their intention, seems to give the customer the opportunity to get 5 bids from contractors...then allows the customer to pick the lowest bid and then demand the highest quality of work, because they feel entitled to since they hired you

It's an easy & fun game to play. You're just pressing buttons to cause an action instantly or watch a short animation, often having the option to skip the animations to quicken things up. It can take a little time to gain & build up the stronger monsters, but it's not difficult. It's a good game to visit once or twice daily, doing quests, join or create a guild, attacking guild dungeon bosses as well as doing Turf War & Confirming Login. If you're doing every activity available, then it's fast & easy to get gold & gems which can help with getting monsters & combining or evolving them into the stronger monsters. Sometimes there are bugs. Sometimes the game crashes, for example I've had the game crash during the Turf War animation. My first experience with the game was loading it up for the first time & quickly discovering it's someone else's account somehow, & I only ever "fixed" it by uninstalling the game from that device & installing it on a different one & really starting new, because making a forum post on their official forums only got suggested ideas from other users which sadly didn't work & I never heard from a Gamevil staff member, & I've been told it's happened before a lot of times for a long time with no fix for it. Currently I have a bug where everytime I open the game it says it has a 0.01mb update to install that installs 104% & I'm not sure what or why that's happening, & also haven't been able to do Turf War at all anymore because it crashes everytime I try. It's not perfect but it's pretty casual & fun. There are micro-transactions for gems & VIP status points towards VIP levels that get you small boosts like an extra attack against bosses or arena or other things. But you can earn VIP points doing a couple things in-game so it's not really pay-to-win, it's sort of pay-to-skip but you'd still have to take the time to do quests to level up & such. I do wish the gem costs of things were a little lower but I've been dealing with it fine, things just need a little more time. The game really opens up as you're getting to level 300, so try to hang onto eggs because then you'll have the chance to hatch higher level monsters. Like I said, it's not a super action heavy game but it's simple & there's not any kind of skill needed besides maybe a little planning. I've been playing it for a couple years on & off, playing once or maybe twice daily to spend my energy & stamina as well as doing all the daily guild things & trying to catch the bosses that open up once a day or once every few days. I've got a few Ragnarok* monsters that I've evolved to get & other normal Ragnarok monsters from combining, as well as many other monsters ranging from high to low quality. I'm still enjoying it. I would probably recommended to anyone that wants a game about building up a monster army that you can visit once or so a day & get everything you need done pretty quickly.
